        <h3><a href="/questions/21112495/why-does-this-works-sometimes-in-python-variable-scope" class="question-hyperlink">why does this works SOMETIMES in python ? (variable scope) [duplicate]</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            This doesn't work: (global name 'a' is not defined)

if True:
  a = 3
else:
  a = 4
print a


This works:

class A:
  def f(self):
    if True:
      a = 3
    else:
      a = 4
    print a

A().f()


...
